        "sentence_id": 29,
        "text": "I\u2014go\u2014to\u2014prepare\u2014a\u2014place\u2014for\u2014you.\u201d  Cicero, when he buried his darling and only daughter, had a heart as full of honest grief as poor Tom\u2019s,\u2014perhaps no fuller, for both were only men;\u2014but Cicero could pause over no such sublime words of hope, and look to no such future reunion; and if he had seen them, ten to one he would not have believed,\u2014he must fill his head first with a thousand questions of authenticity of manuscript, and correctness of translation.",
